pg11: Goals:
We’re building a dynamic and collaborative platform to keep an up-to-date database of all likeminded community innovation spaces, and to encourage more networking and linkages amongst these spaces worldwide. We’ve standardized a set of datafields and built an API in conjunction with Rob Baker’s Maker.json, so all data hosted on the Atlas can be easily shared across other sites. We’re in the process of turning this platform into an open-access wiki, to keep everything up-to-date through crowdsourced submissions and moderators.
 
What’s a “community innovation space”?
Ð	A community of people eager to collaborate with others— the space must be either open to the public or available for outside partnerships
Ð	Support for old and/or new technological innovation, including hardware, software, metal-working, handicrafts, design thinking, repurposed trash, farming, etc.
Ð	A physical or virtual space (or temporary event) that promotes creativity and nurtures new ideas
 
